Robot Framework installation

Check Python Version above 3
pip3 install robotframework==3.2.2
pip3 install robotframework-seleniumlibrary  (5.1.3)
pip3 uninstall robotframework
Check robotframework==3.2.2 version
Check Eclipse Version
Install Red Robot Editor from help->marketplace
restart after installation
window->perspective->select robot
window->preferences->robot framework->installed framework->select 3.2.2
file->new->robot project
create->new folder on project called Tests.
create new robot test suite.
program:
First TestCase
    Log  Welcome
check output log

Day-2

For Chrome driver - https://chromedriver.chromium.org/downloads
Download for the same version in system (93)
Copy the extracted file to usr/local/bin location.
Link used for testing - https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/login
Include selenium library for using the driver also add in the red.xml to resolve the error (use quick fix)
Link for examples: https://robotframework.org/SeleniumLibrary/SeleniumLibrary.html
CSS-Selector: https://www.w3schools.com/cssref/css_selectors.asp





